Submodules¶

scripts.FortSummerProblem module¶

Created on 28 May 2017

Code to debug the delay in the estimated target RA,DEC crossings seen on Fort Summer. It’s already been solved!

@author: Marc Casalprim

scripts.altitude module¶

Created on Jun 22, 2017

Altitude scripts without indexing, because we dont have a valid index for GpsReadings (approximatmceFN is empty)

@author: Marc Casalprim

Plot, delay lines control loops

@author: Marc Casalprim

@author: Marc Casalprim

scripts.idCcmgs module¶

Created on 30 may. 2017

Generates a dataset including CCMGinput, wheelsAngle and Gyros and saves it on a .mat file. Useful for model identification, or finding the Inertia value in MatLab.

@author: Marc Casalprim

scripts.mceArchives module¶

Created on Jun 22, 2017

Prints the frame numbers that are in each Archive inside the root_folder

@author: Marc Casalprim

scripts.plotField module¶

Created on Jun 22, 2017

Plot data from a field, using DataSet class. Merging archives if we want.

@author: Marc Casalprim

scripts.plotFieldFiltered module¶

Created on Jun 22, 2017

Plot data from a field. The peaks of field data are filtered using utils.dataset.filterArray. Merging archives if we want.

@author: Marc Casalprim

scripts.plotFieldNoTime module¶

Created on Jun 22, 2017

Plot raw data from a field. Without time. Useful when the archive ended abruptly and the dimensions do not match. Merging archives if we want.

@author: Marc Casalprim

scripts.plotFieldRaw module¶

Created on Jun 22, 2017

Plot raw data from a field. Merging archives if we want.

@author: Marc Casalprim

scripts.plotFlightArchivesMerged module¶

Created on 28 jun. 2017

Script for scripts simultaneously data from different archives

@author: Marc Casalprim

scripts.telescopeRADEC module¶

Created on 23 May 2017

Plot and save telescope RA and DEC

@author: Marc Casalprim

scripts.thermometersByNumberCharacterized module¶

Created on 10 jul. 2017

Script for plotting thermometers data from different archives. The thermometers calssified in different groups by their mean temperature and also plotted by data flatness.

@author: Marc Casalprim

scripts.thermometersByNumberCharacterized.flatness(x)¶

scripts.thermometersCubicSpline module¶

Created on 10 jul. 2017

Script for plotting thermometers from a single folder. Interpolating the data with cubic splines to have uniform time steps.

@author: Marc Casalprim
